race.comment: THE SMASH FACTOR (4) won his Maiden easily here this trip and then led this grade over 1700m at the track claimed late. Is likely to take a sit today and can bounce back. JENNI INTIBA (5) comes out of the same race and got too far back for the new yard. Had been solid at the provincials prior and will be suited stepping up to the middle distance. Has the winkers on for the first time and can fight out the finish. DIGARI (2) spiked his numbers missing a whisker at Horsham over 1800m when he led. The niggle is the extra 200m but he's on the improve and has to be considered. SQUANDER (8) is capable of better and may be the best of the remainder.
